<chapter
	id="management">

	<title>Managing &THIS.PLATFORM; Diameter with &MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM;</title>

	<section id="main_view">
		<title>&MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM; Diameter Plugin Main View</title>
		<para>This section describes the main view of &MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM; Diameter Plugin.</para>
		
		<para>In order to access this, go to the top menu and select <menuchoice><guimenu>Resources</guimenu><guisubmenu>Servers</guisubmenu></menuchoice>. A list should be presented, where &THIS.PLATFORM; Diameter is present. Click it to access server details.</para>
		
		<para>You should have something similar to the following figure:</para>

		<figure>
			<title>&MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM; Diameter Plugin Main View.</title>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="images/img-jopr_diameter_main_view.png" format="PNG"/>
				</imageobject>
				<textobject>
					<para>&MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM; Diameter Plugin Main View</para>
				</textobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</figure>

		<para>As you can see in the left side menu you have the following components that can be managed by &MANAGEMENT.PLATFORM;:</para>

		<itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>Stack (Parent)</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>Local Peer ([LP] ...)</para>
      </listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Network Peers ([NP] ...)</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Realms (FQDN)</para>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>

		<para>Each one will be described and explained in it's own section.</para>

	</section>
	
